    <item>
      <title>Unlocking the origins and biology of domestic animals using ancient DNA and paleogenomics</title>
      <link>/post/adna-domestication-review/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 02 Dec 2019 03:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>/post/adna-domestication-review/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;a href=&#34;/publication/unlocking-the-origins-and-biology-of-domestic-animals-using-ancient-dna-and-paleogenomics/&#34; title=&#34;See publication&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;review&lt;/a&gt; on the use of ancient DNA for studying the evolution of domesticated animal species has been published in &lt;a href=&#34;https://bmcbiol.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12915-019-0724-7&#34; title=&#34;See paper&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;BMC Biology&lt;/em&gt;,&lt;/a&gt; DOI: &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1186/s12915-019-0724-7&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;10.1186/s12915-019-0724-7&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/a&gt; It has also been mentioned in some news &lt;a href=&#34;https://gizmodo.com/famous-foxes-bred-for-tameness-weren-t-actually-wild-in-1840266655&#34; title=&#34;See article&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;articles&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
